  "text": "The measured reference flow from the 2D through-plane PC measurements were used as input to CFD simulations. The CFD simulations were performed using ANSYS Fluent 14 (Ansys Inc., Canonsburg PA). The governing equations were discretized using a second-order finite volume method, and the pressure-velocity coupling was done using the SIMPLE algorithm [CITATION_1] . The computational geometry is a two-dimensional axisymmetric representation of the tube, 40 tube diameters long. The stenosis was placed midway between the inlet and outlet.",
